(Placeholder reference — backup archives are typically not committed to GitHub.)

Lab assumption:
- A previously created archive named: backup.tar.gz
- Verified present using: ls -lh backup.tar.gz
- Restored using: tar -xzvf backup.tar.gz -C restored_backup_directory/

In production repositories:
- Store backups in dedicated backup storage (object storage, backup server, vault)
- Keep only scripts, checks, and verification logs in GitHub
